# Cursor QA Observer

Cursor monitors and validates ForgeOS locally. Codex owns implementation unless the user explicitly assigns a small fix to Cursor.

## Do

- Run the app locally (`npm run dev`); inspect via Cursor browser.
- Capture reproducible defects with evidence (console, network, viewport, screenshots).
- Run deterministic checks: `npm run lint`, `npm run typecheck`, `npm run test`.
- Write structured findings under `.qa/findings/` and scoped Codex tasks under `.qa/tasks/`.
- Report missing orchestration only when `npm run agent:health` or `npm run agent:maintain` are unavailable.

## Do not

- Broad refactors, speculative styling, or subjective design changes without acceptance criteria.
- Auto-fix issues unless explicitly instructed and Codex is not active on the same files.
- Run heavy builds and full suites in parallel on this machine.

## Viewports for responsive QA

- Desktop 1440×900, tablet 1024×768, mobile 390×844.

## Finding format

Use the ForgeOS QA Finding template (ID `FORGE-QA-XXX`) documented in `.qa/README.md`.
